title: Breast Cancer Screening and Management (BCSM) Clinical Decision Support (CDS) Implementation Guide

grouping.name: Primary Screening Decision
grouping.description: Resources related to PrimaryScreeningDecision mid-level flow

resource.name: 5 Year Risk Assessment Request
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a ServiceRequest to perform a 5 year risk assessment.

resource.name: Average Risk
resource.description: Patient population identified as average risk. Provides criteria to determine age to start, screening modality, and screening interval for these populations of patients.

resource.name: Biopsy Result Observation Code System
resource.description: Code representing breast cancer biopsy result observations

resource.name: Breast Cancer Decision to Screen Questionnaire
resource.description: A questionnaire to assess factors related to breast cancer routine screening.

resource.name: Breast Cancer Genetic Risk Referral Questionnaire
resource.description: A questionnaire to assess familial risk factors related to breast cancer.

resource.name: Breast Cancer High Risk Referral Questionnaire
resource.description: A questionnaire to assess risk factors related to breast cancer.

resource.name: Breast Cancer Screening Service Request
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a ServiceRequest for screening study, biopsy procedure or specialty referral.

resource.name: Communicate Eligible
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a CommunicationRequest containing information about the patient's ineligibility for screening.

resource.name: Communicate Not Eligible
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a CommunicationRequest containing information about the patient's ineligibility for screening.

resource.name: Communicate Shared Decision Making to Continue Screening
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a CommunicationRequest recommending shared decision making on the decision to continue screening.

resource.name: Communicate Shared Decision Making to Continue Screening
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a CommunicationRequest recommending shared decision making on the decision to refer for high risk evaluation.

resource.name: Communicate Shared Decision Making to Delay Screening
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a CommunicationRequest recommending shared decision making on the decision to delay screening.

resource.name: Decision to Screen
resource.description: Evaluate criteria to determine age to start and age to stop, screening modality, and screening interval.

resource.name: Followup Screening Result
resource.description: Determines next steps, if any, based on result of screening imaging or biopsy. This may be triggered by a diagnostic report being received by the system or an imaging BI-RADS result being documented in a structured manner.

resource.name: Genetic Counseling Referral Request
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a ServiceRequest for genetic counseling referral.

resource.name: Genetic Risk Assessment Request
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a ServiceRequest to perform a genetic risk assessment.

resource.name: Genetic Risk Referral
resource.description: Risk assessment for women who have family history that may be associated with an increased risk for potentially harmful mutations in breast cancer susceptibility genes to determine who should receive referral for genetic counseling and, if indicated after counseling, testing.

resource.name: High Level Flow
resource.description: High Level Flow pathway.

resource.name: High Risk Exclusions
resource.description: Clinical characteristics that have been identified in the USPSTF breast screening recommendation statement as indicative of higher than average risk and therefore excluded from recommendation statement patient population. Provides criteria to determine age to start and age to stop, screening modality, and screening interval for these populations of patients.

resource.name: High Risk Referral
resource.description: Women who are at increased risk for breast cancer without current or previous diagnosis of breast cancer or ductal carcinoma in situ (DCIS) can be referred to a breast specialty clinic to consider risk reduction interventions.

resource.name: High Risk Specialty Referral Request
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a ServiceRequest for high risk breast specialty referral.

resource.name: Plan Definition Action Code System
resource.description: Code representing plan definition action codes

resource.name: Plan Definition Action Codes
resource.description: This value set includes action codes for Plan Definitions within this implementation guide.

resource.name: Plan Definition Action Reason Codes
resource.description: This value set includes action reason codes for Plan Definitions within this implementation guide.

resource.name: Primary Screening Decision
resource.description: Primary Screening Decision pathway.

resource.name: Recommendation Flag Code System
resource.description: Code representing due/overdue flags

resource.name: Recommendation Flag Codes
resource.description: This value set includes flag codes for recommendation actions within this implementation guide.

resource.name: Recommendation Flag Extension
resource.description: An extension that holds a Due/Overdue flag CodeableConcept value.

resource.name: Screening Due Measure
resource.description:
Identifies patient who may be due for screening based on prior assessment and documentation of next due date and flags patient who may be overdue for potential enhanced outreach efforts.

Intended for use with either individual patient alerts, within the context of a clinical encounter or outside an encounter, or for generating asynchronous reports on a cohort/panel of patients in order to target outreach or escalation.

resource.name: Screening Eligible
resource.description:
Determines whether a patient is eligible for routine breast cancer screening. This includes absolute exclusion criteria for which routine screening is not indicated in all guidelines and pathways.

Individuals who have certain signs or symptoms concerning for breast cancer or other breast diseases are excluded from routine screening pathways and should have diagnostic testing performed.

resource.name: Screening Eligible Questionnaire Task
resource.description: This ActivityDefinition generates a Questionnaire Task containing a request to complete a questionnaire.

resource.name: Screening Observation Code System
resource.description: Code representing breast cancer screening related observations

resource.name: Screening Test Incomplete Measure
resource.description:
Identifies patients who have been ordered for screening mammography or for follow-up study for abnormal screening mammography but for whom a study report has not been received or documented as received.

Intended for use with either individual patient alerts, within the context of a clinical encounter or outside an encounter, or for generating asynchronous reports on a cohort/panel of patients in order to target outreach or escalation.

resource.name: Special Populations
resource.description:
Patient population that have been identified as higher than average risk or otherwise requiring specific consideration within a particular guideline. 

Provides criteria to determine age to start, screening modality, and screening interval for these populations of patients.
